The paper deals with the verification of algorithms for And-Inverter Graphs (AIGs), which are commonly used in hardware verification tools. This suggests that the paper could belong to the Logic in Computer Science (cs.LO) sub-category. Additionally, the paper discusses the implementation of these algorithms in the ACL2 theorem prover, which could fall under the Programming Languages (cs.PL) or Embedded Systems (cs.ET) sub-categories. The paper also mentions the use of SAT solvers, which could relate to the Automated Reasoning (cs.AR) sub-category. Finally, the paper discusses the practical benefits of their work for ACL2 users, which could fall under the Software Engineering (cs.SE) sub-category.
